  "text": "For chondrogenic differentiation, 4 × 10 5 MSCs were centrifuged in polypropylene tubes to form a pelleted micromass and maintained in chondrogenic induction medium consisting of α-MEM supplemented with 10 −7 M dexamethasone, 1% (vol/vol) insulin-transferrin-sodium selenite, 50 µM ascorbate-2 phosphate, 1 mM sodium pyruvate, 50 µg/ml (wt/vol) proline, and 20 ng/ ml (wt/vol) TGF-β3. On day 21, the pellets were fixed and sectioned as previously described [CITATION_1] . The development of chondrocytes and accumulation of the cartilage matrix were evaluated by toluidine blue staining.",
